        "client_msg_id": "bf74d2ed-5e84-41db-8d41-2ba9b3cfdc29",
        "text": "At the R Contribution Working Group we discussed quite a lot about translations: <https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/rcwg\/blob\/main\/team_minutes\/2023-09-15.md>.\n\nOne discussion was following up on the idea of applying for funding to the R Consortium to support translations work as suggested by <@U01ERR6MN9G>. There are some tricky issues to work out here and it seems unlikely that we have the capacity to pull something together in time for the Oct 1 deadline - at least that was the consensus at the meeting. So unless someone else here has the ideas and energy to push this forward now, it will probably have to wait till a later round.\n\nHowever, <@U027JEHGZRA> suggested asking for funding for local hackathons, which could potentially be done under the Special Projects fund (<https:\/\/www.r-consortium.org\/all-projects\/r-user-group-support-program>). This avoids a lot of the issues, e.g. supports anyone that contributes, funds could be managed via a local R group, more flexible deadline to apply for funding. So something to consider for anyone wanting to organize such events.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "g580131f5a7a",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/580131f5a7a4fa33c811dc6d20ab3ef8.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0004-72.png",
